Mergers and acquisitions are given an extra test in due diligence: cybersecurity. Buyers and investors are increasingly demanding demonstrable digital resilience – and this has everything to do with risks that would otherwise only become visible after an acquisition. Why cybersecurity has become decisive. Buyers do not want a digital time bomb: systems must be safe, incidents must be handled properly, chain risks must be controlled. Companies without certification or with vulnerabilities in their supplier network are at risk of:
the deal is canceled;
the value is adjusted;
or substantial guarantees are required.

